**For fresh NixOS installation:**

1. Boot the NixOS installer ISO
2. Partition and format your disks (or let the installer handle it)
3. Clone your config repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-config /mnt/etc/nixos
   ```
4. Install NixOS with your flake:
   ```bash
   sudo nixos-install --flake /mnt/etc/nixos#{{HOSTNAME}}
   ```
5. Reboot and log in with the initial password (change it immediately!)

See the [Installation Guide](https://github.com/kcalvelli/axios/blob/master/docs/INSTALLATION.md) for detailed instructions.

## Updating

### Updating Packages and System

To update all packages to their latest versions:

```bash
update-flake      # Update all flake inputs
rebuild-switch    # Apply updates
```

Or manually:
```bash
nix flake update
rebuild-switch
```

### Updating axiOS Framework

To update to the latest version of axios:

```bash
# Update only axios (keeps other inputs at current versions)
nix flake lock --update-input axios
rebuild-switch
```

Or update everything at once:
```bash
update-flake      # Updates axios + all other inputs
rebuild-switch
```

**Check for breaking changes:**
- Review [axios releases](https://github.com/kcalvelli/axios/releases) before updating
- Check release notes for any required configuration changes
- Test updates with `rebuild-test` before committing

**Rollback if needed:**
```bash
sudo nixos-rebuild switch --rollback
```

